# ==========================================================================
# Root build context filter for the API image.
#
# Railway builds the Dockerfile with the REPOSITORY ROOT as the context, so
# without this file the entire frontend — including web/node_modules and
# web/.next — would be uploaded to the builder on every deploy. That is
# hundreds of megabytes the API image never reads.
#
# This is a plain deny-list rather than an "exclude everything, then
# re-include" allow-list. Allow-lists in .dockerignore depend on subtle
# pattern/parent-directory precedence, and getting them wrong fails the build
# with a confusing "file not found" on a COPY. Listing what to drop is duller
# and much harder to break.
# ==========================================================================

# --- The frontend and docs: never part of the API image -------------------
web
docs

# --- Dependencies and build output (restored/created inside the build) ----
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.next
**/.turbo

# --- Secrets: must never enter an image layer -----------------------------
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# --- VCS, tooling and editor noise ----------------------------------------
.git
.gitignore
.github
**/.DS_Store
**/*.log
**/npm-debug.log*
**/coverage
**/.vscode
**/.idea

# --- Deployment config not read by the build ------------------------------
README.md
railway.toml
server/render.yaml
server/README.md

# The API's own Dockerfile, used for standalone builds from inside server/.
# The root Dockerfile is the one Railway builds.
server/Dockerfile
server/.dockerignore
